ğŸ“– Lesson Content
â€¢ Jurisdiction as Gatekeeper ğŸšª â€” Courts can refuse to hear cases by declaring lack of subject matter or personal jurisdiction.
â€¢ Jurisdiction as Weapon ğŸ—¡ï¸ â€” Opponents will argue jurisdictional defects to avoid the merits, especially against pro se litigants.
â€¢ Jurisdiction as Strategy ğŸ§­ â€” Raising jurisdictional issues early, framing them clearly, and preserving them on appeal turns the opponentâ€™s weapon into your shield.
ğŸ“ Assignment
Draft a Notice of Jurisdictional Challenge. It should:
1. Identify the specific jurisdictional defect (subject matter, personal, or venue).
2. Cite the relevant rule or statute.
3. Preserve the objection for the record.

âœ… Model Answer (Example)
