ğŸ“– Lesson Content
â€¢ Timing & Targets â±ï¸ğŸ¯ â€” File objections within 14 days: to a magistrate judgeâ€™s Report & Recommendation under Rule 72(b)(2) / 28 U.S.C. Â§ 636(b)(1), and to nonâ€‘dispositive orders under Rule 72(a). Request a short stay if you need transcripts to finalize specifics.
â€¢ Specificity & Standard ğŸ“ â€” Be specific. Cite page/line and ECF/Exhibit pinâ€‘cites. For 72(b): de novo review of the objected portions. For 72(a): the district judge must modify or set aside parts that are clearly erroneous or contrary to law.
â€¢ Make the Record ğŸ§¾ â€” Number each objection; tie facts to law; attach key exhibits; and propose the corrected ruling. Failure to object specifically can waive appellate review.
ğŸ“ Assignment
