Module 24 â€“ The Pro Se Trap â€” and How to Escape It with Format ğŸ•³ï¸ğŸ§©
âš–ï¸ Core Message
Courts say they â€˜liberally construeâ€™ pro se filingsâ€”but the docket runs on format. The trap is thinking substance alone will carry you. The escape is **format**: captions, certificates, pinâ€‘cites, proposed orders, and rules compliance.

ğŸ“– Lesson Content
â€¢ Trap #1: Narrative â‰  Motion â€” A heartfelt story without Rule 7(b) grounds and specific relief is easy to deny or ignore.
â€¢ Trap #2: Missing Pieces â€” No caption, no signature block, no certificate of service, no proposed order, no exhibit index.
â€¢ Trap #3: Offâ€‘Record Evidence â€” Screenshots or emails never filed become invisible on appeal.
â€¢ Trap #4: Local Rule Landmines â€” Page limits, conferral statements, font/margins, and deadlines (and Rule 6(b) for extensions).
â€¢ Trap #5: Silence â‰  Safety â€” Failure to object, to notice appeal, or to move to supplement the record waives issues.
â€¢ Escape Plan: Format First â€” (1) Write the proposed order; (2) draft Issue â†’ Grounds (law + pinâ€‘cites) â†’ Relief; (3) attach declarations/exhibits with an index; (4) add certificate of service; (5) check local rules; (6) file a clean PDF and keep proof.
ğŸ“ Assignment
